Well, the first two confusingly change two variables at once: the things that are the same (which I presume is what kimundi meant) are<p><pre><code>    fn foo<S, T: MyTrait<S>>(elem: T) { ... }

    fn foo<S, T>(elem: T) where T: MyTrait<S> { ... }
</code></pre>
and<p><pre><code>    fn foo<S, T: MyTrait<Thing = S>>(elem: T) { ... }

    fn foo<S, T>(elem: T) where T: MyTrait<Thing = S> { ... }</code></pre>
